HB 2406 Oct 16: Second Officer C.G. van der Berg, of the Netherland steamer Magdala, Capt. J. de Klerk, reports that a radio message was received from the British motor ship Lochmonar, on May 15, 1935, atating that at 16.20 G.M.T., in lat. 33°43'30"N., lon. 48°47'00"W., a growler had been sighted, approximately 90 feet long, 25 feet wide, with its highest point showing about 3' above water. Temperature of the air 68°F. Note: Information was received from Capt. H. Womersley, of the Lochmonar, on Oct. 3, 1935 verifying the above report and further stating that the growler was passed at a distance of 3/4 of a mile, & that the weather was fine, clear, & cloudless. The temperature of the water was 68°F.; sea smooth with a slight NW swell; barometer 30.11 inches.
